    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2405" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δίκη</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">usage,
            custom</span>, hence <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">right, justice;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὕτη δίκη ἐστὶ βροτῶν</span>, the ‘inevitable
          way,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 11.218</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; μνηστήρων οὐχ ἥδε δίκη τὸ πάροιθε
            τέτυκτο,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 18.275</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ἣ
            γὰρ δίκη, ὁππότε πάτρης</span> | <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἧς ἀπέῃσιν
            ἀνήρ,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 19.168</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            δίκῃ ἠμείψατο</span>, ‘in the way of justice,’ ‘with an appeal to
          justice,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 23.542</span></i>; pl.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">judgments, decisions</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            11.570</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
